I am new to WebGL, ThreeJS, and GIT and I'm just having a dandy of a time with command-line tools (such as git rebase) as well as trying to master your APIs (which i intend to add my own flavor to) along with pure WebGLs syntax, which the new editor will be able to export as ...

I'm trying to make the APIs as self-documenting and as clear and concise as possible for someone whom has never seen ThreeJS or WebGL ..and your editor will be able to do that,eg

var geometry = new THREE.BoxBufferGeometry( 1, 1, 1 );
var material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( {color: 0x00ff00} );
var cube = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material );
scene.add( cube );

-->

var geometry = new THREE.Geometry.Cube( {width:1, height:1, depth:1} );
var material = new THREE.MeshMaterial.Basic( {color: 0x00ff00} );
var cube = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material );
scene.add( cube );

I plan to add a gl state generator on the backend of the Editor's Undo/Redo buffer to generate the following as an example

THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.material.mesh.lambert.color.hexadecimal = 0xff0000 // eg. cannot be created without a geometry and/or texture
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.width.float = 1
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.height.float = 1
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.depth.float = 1
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.position.posX.float = -4
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.position.posY.float = 3
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.geometry.position.posZ.float = 0
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.position.posX.float = 15
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.position.posY.float = 0
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.position.posZ.float = 0
THREE.WebGL.context.3d.renderer.render.scene.cube.shadow.cast.bool = true

..the inference engine will then infer lean WebGL.
